The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Vettori all the way
                                                   Vettori all the way
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: New Zealand captain Daniel Vettori has reasonable claim to the title of best number eight batsman in the history of Test cricket. Vettori has moved up four places to a career-high 26th position in the LG ICC Player Rankings for Test batsmen on 608 ratings points, the best rating by a regular number eight batsman in the history of the game.         
